snippet: Callers overwhelmed the enrollment system on Monday, so officials recorded their telephone numbers with plans to call them back to sign up for health insurance before Tuesday’s deadline.
abstract: United States officials say record number of Americans are trying to enroll for health insurance under Affordable Care Act ahead of Jan deadline.
lead_paragraph: Callers overwhelmed the enrollment system on Monday, so officials recorded their telephone numbers with plans to call them back to sign up for health insurance before Tuesday’s deadline.

headline.main: As Health Care Act Insurance Deadline Nears, ‘Unprecedented Demand’
headline.print_headline: Health Insurance Demand Surges on Eve of Deadline
